    "Holden Spaht is a managing partner at software-focused private equity firm Thoma Bravo, which was ranked as the world's top buyout investor in a 2019 report.",
    "The firm, with assets of $131 billion, was formed in 2008, when Orlando Bravo and Carl Thoma split from partner Brian Cressey, who was focused on healthcare deals.",
    "Spaht, who holds an MBA from Harvard, has led many of the firm's application software investments.",
    "He joined Thoma Bravo in 2005 after stints at Thomas H Lee Partners and Morgan Stanley Capital Partners.",
    "His family foundation supports mental health, the environment and the arts; it is the lead donor for Lindley Center, a health and counseling clinic named for his younger sister."
